content: Good point-and-click game, nice time killer for kids
I've played the whole series so far,good graphics,and story line

As the rest of the series, this game has a great storyline and some tricky puzzles. I can't stand hidden object scenes, but in 5BN games at least they are a bit creative and interactive, not just stupidly find items in a scene. It's shorter than the earlier Lost Lands games though, and the cutscenes are terribly blurry on my tablet (Samsung Galaxy Tab S3). Since the increase in price, I delay purchase until they are on sale. Pity they don't come with a reduced introductory price, as is quite common practise with other companies.

I've really enjoyed the lost lands series and this is another five-bn success. We've gotten to know the characters and the shock end in this one is making me hope number 6 will be out soon. It had the usual collectibles, morphing objects, map and bonus chapter. I would still love more mini games as this only had 19 but I liked the puzzles in the extra section after you've completed the main and bonus games. Overall a good game that's enjoyable and helps you forget 'real life' for a few hours.
